After being together for 7yrs, Kidsgrove FC Galaxy are looking for players to join our family as we move into U15’s (School Year 10 in September) for then 2019/20 season.

Last season we were runners up in a closely fought title race in the NSJYL Yellow League. So for next season we’ll be looking to be promoted to the Red (Top) League for U15s.

We have an FA Level 1 coach with full DBS & Safeguarding certificates. 
If you’re interested in finding out more then please contact me via Facebook or the Manager Grant on 07398 231073

** And some late news from Monday evening ** I’m sorry #Grassroots but after a fabulous first season, @stokecity get to keep Zara for another year as she’s signed a contract with @scfc_ladies Under 10s

I’ve not posted on my walking for a little while..... As you know back in March I took part in Walk All Over Cancer on behalf of @cr_uk where the challenge was to complete at least 10,000 steps every single day of that month. Well it’s now two and a half months later and I’m still completing at least 10,000 steps a day and making sure my @fitbituk_ireland dashboard has a bank of green too! 🚶🏻‍♂️👣🚶🏻‍♂️👣 At the same time, at the start of March I set myself a goal weight to aim at! It’s of course my target so not a recognised one but yesterday I hit it 😃 - it takes me from a starting weight at obese to a low over weight or as my lad says from ‘fat as......’ to just fat (he’s grounded!) My target weight? 
15st 7lb, so I’ve now lost a little over 24lb!!! 😱

What’s next? 
A few days of maintaining the target weight (I may have had the usual chippy tea last night and some sweets to celebrate) Then it’s time to do what all good clients do - move the goalposts!!! New target weight to be confirmed but I’m aiming to be in the Healthy Weight band (without having to wear platform shoes to make me taller of course 😂) Maybe some jogging/running too; although I’ll need some advice with my ‘glass’ ankles!

On a more serious note my charity page is still open and I’d love it if anyone that hasn’t already then please sponsor me a little. I mean you now know that I blitz March and beyond!! Please click the link in my bio

Thanks to you all for the support and encouragement over the last few months

#WalkAllOverCancer #steps #charity #stillgoingstrong #walkfatladwalk #weightloss #WalkForrestWalk

Well that’s March done and I’ve completed Walk All Over Cancer for @cr_uk Yes, believe it not, this fat lad has completed over 10,000 steps every single day for the month come rain or shine! 
Many, many thanks to those who’ve taken the time to sponsor me and if you’ve haven’t had chance yet (or thought I wouldn’t complete it) then there’s still time as I’ll keep the page open for a little longer.. See the link in my bio

What’s even more enlightening that during the month I’ve also lost a stone!! (just.....) which has got to be a benefit and with that in mind, I may just keep on walking.... #WalkAllOverCancer #steps #charity
Well @dclarke1974 as if this was 6 years ago!!! It really was a great day and catch up, thankfully we’ve seen each other a little bit more in this last 6 years.
